          <h3 class="ba-title">Copy.ai — Best for sales and marketing copy at volume</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For small teams that need to produce high-volume marketing copy across ads, emails, and landing pages — not long-form editorial blog content.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Copy.ai's GTM workflows automate multi-step marketing sequences. The workflow builder chains AI tasks — research, draft, personalize — without manual steps between them. Strong for sales teams running outbound at volume. Less suited to editorial content marketing. Blog article output from Copy.ai requires more editing than Jasper or Letterdrop. Right tool if your team focuses on short-form; wrong tool if blog is the primary channel.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>GTM Workflows for high-volume marketing automation</h4><p>The most powerful workflow builder in the AI copy category. Sequences multiple AI tasks with data inputs between steps — better than any single-prompt tool.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Best for short-form across 50+ ad and email formats</h4><p>Ad copy, email subject lines, product descriptions, social captions. For volume short-form production, Copy.ai is the fastest tool in this list.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Unlimited users on higher-tier plans</h4><p>Scale plan includes unlimited seats. Good for growing teams that don't want per-seat pricing to scale costs with headcount.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: long-form blog output needs heavy editing</h4><p>Long-form articles from Copy.ai consistently require more revision than other tools. If blog SEO is a primary growth channel, Copy.ai is not the right production tool.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

