      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What are the best content marketing tools for small teams?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">theStacc is the best for teams that need blog output without writers — 30 articles per month for $99/mo. CoSchedule is the best editorial calendar. Jasper is the best AI writing assistant. Surfer SEO is the best optimization layer. Buffer is the best free social scheduling tool. Most small teams benefit from theStacc for content production plus one scheduling tool for social.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How do small teams produce enough content to compete?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">The small teams that outperform don't outwork larger departments — they automate the high-volume tasks. Blog writing, social scheduling, and SEO optimization can all be automated. A 2-person team running theStacc publishes more content per month than a 10-person department using manual workflows.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How much should a small team budget for content marketing tools?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">$200–$500/month is a realistic range for a 2–5 person team. theStacc at $99/month handles blog production. Add Surfer SEO ($89) and Buffer ($18) for a complete content operation under $210/month. Avoid enterprise stacks — they charge $2,000/month for features a small team won't use.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can small teams publish blog content without a writer?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. theStacc publishes 30 SEO-optimized blog articles per month without any writing from your team. Topics are researched based on your industry and competitors. Articles publish directly to WordPress, Webflow, or Ghost. No briefs, no drafts to review, no CMS upload required.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What's the biggest content marketing bottleneck for small teams?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Blog production. A single SEO blog post takes 3–5 hours to research, write, edit, and optimize. At 4 posts per month, that's 12–20 hours — 30–50% of a small marketer's capacity. theStacc eliminates that bottleneck entirely: 30 articles published per month without your team writing a single word.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What content marketing tools are free for small teams?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Buffer (free for 3 channels), Canva (250,000+ templates free), Google Analytics 4 (free), and ChatGPT (free plan for caption writing) cover social scheduling, design, and analytics without spending a dollar. Blog content production still requires a paid tool or writer — theStacc at $99/month is the most cost-effective option.</div>
